[SN]TITLE[SN]
Wigan Warriors rugby team using ballet in training

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Rugby league team Wigan Warriors' Under-19s players have started taking weekly ballet classes.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
22 February 2017 Last updated at 12:05 GMT
It's to help improve their strength and posture and reduce injury to their ankles and knees.
The team say they're enjoying it and they've noticed a difference in their strength thanks to the training.
Their ballet teacher hopes more professional teams in the UK will take up ballet.
